summary: This is an email from a legal team (likely prosecutors) transmitting a public version of a Rule 16(d) letter in the Maxwell case and a Local Rule 16.1 affidavit for review. It indicates ongoing pre-trial discovery and procedural filings in the criminal prosecution of Ghislaine Maxwell.

events.title: Transmission of 16(d) Letter and Affidavit in Maxwell Case
events.description: A public version of a Rule 16(d) letter and a Local Rule 16.1 affidavit in the Ghislaine Maxwell case are sent for review via email.

keyFacts: A Rule 16(d) letter and Local Rule 16.1 affidavit were prepared in the Ghislaine Maxwell case as of October 1, 2020.
The documents were transmitted in a public version, indicating they were intended for court filing or disclosure.
The email shows the procedural and pre-trial discovery phase of the Maxwell prosecution was active at this date.
